            <div type="note" subtype="biographical">
                <head type="title"> <persName corresp="#JCL">John Claudius Loudon</persName> (<date notBefore="1783" notAfter="1843">1783&#x2013;1843</date>)</head>
                <p>A near contemporary of <persName corresp="#JJR">John James Ruskin</persName>, <persName corresp="#JCL">Loudon</persName> was born in <placeName corresp="#LANARKSHIRE">Lanarkshire</placeName>, and he studied in <placeName corresp="#EDINBURGH">Edinburgh</placeName> as a youth, 
                    drawn early to the horticultural interests that led to his career as a landscape designer and as a writer and editor on gardening, 
                    horticulture, and other fields of natural history.</p>
                
            </div>
